## Learn: Cross-Sections of 3D Figures

### Key Concept: Cross-Sections of a Cube

| Slice Direction | Cross-Section |
|----------------|---------------|
| Parallel to a face | Square |
| Perpendicular to a face through midpoints | Rectangle |
| Diagonal through four vertices | Rectangle |
| Through six edges at equal angles | Regular hexagon |
| Through three vertices | Triangle (equilateral if cut properly) |

### Key Concept: Cross-Sections of a Cylinder

| Slice Direction | Cross-Section |
|----------------|---------------|
| Parallel to base | Circle |
| Perpendicular to base | Rectangle |
| At an angle (not parallel or perpendicular) | Ellipse |

### Key Concept: Cross-Sections of a Cone

| Slice Direction | Cross-Section |
|----------------|---------------|
| Parallel to base | Circle |
| Perpendicular to base through apex | Triangle |
| At an angle | Ellipse, parabola, or hyperbola (conic sections) |

### Key Concept: Cavalieri's Principle

If two solids have the same height and the same cross-sectional area at every level, then they have the same volume, even if the shapes are different.

