## Example 3 — Volume of Composite Solid (Cylinder + Hemisphere)

A capsule-shaped solid consists of a cylinder of radius 3 cm and height 10 cm with a hemisphere on each end. Find the total volume.

### Step 1: Volume of the Cylinder

$$V_{\text{cyl}} = \pi r^2 h = \pi(3)^2(10) = 90\pi$$

### Step 2: Volume of the Two Hemispheres

Two hemispheres = one full sphere:

$$V_{\text{sphere}} = \frac{4}{3}\pi r^3 = \frac{4}{3}\pi(27) = 36\pi$$

### Step 3: Total Volume

$$V_{\text{total}} = 90\pi + 36\pi = 126\pi \approx 395.84 \text{ cm}^3$$

### Step 4: Verify

The capsule shape is a common pharmaceutical design. The cylindrical middle holds $90\pi$ cm³ and the two rounded ends hold $36\pi$ cm³ combined. ✓

✅ Answer: Total volume is $126\pi \approx$ **395.84 cm³**.

